All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Redis
The Redis class is responsible for centralizing the constant values used throughout the library and providing utility methods.
Redis.DistanceUnit
RedisCore geo units
Redis.Document
RedisSearch document storage options
Redis.Encryption
RedisCore encryption options
Redis.Function
RedisTimeSeries functions
RedisCore
The RedisCore class is responsible for accessing the core Redis commands via the Jedis programmatic library.
RedisCypher
RedisCypher is a helper class responsible for generating Cipher syntax from DataGraph objects.
RedisDoc
The RedisDoc class handles Redis database operations centered around DataDoc objects.
RedisDS
The Redis Data Source class manages connections with one or more Redis Server processes.
RedisDSException
A RedisDSException and its subclasses are a form of Throwable that indicates conditions that an application developer might want to catch.
RedisField
The RedisField class handles Redis hash field name generation and restoration operations.
RedisGraphs
The RedisGraphs class is responsible for accessing the RedisGraph module commands via the Jedis programmatic library.
RedisGrid
The RedisGrid class handles Redis database operations centered around DataGrid objects.
RedisItem
The RedisItem class handles Redis database operations centered around DataItem objects.
RedisJson
The RedisJson class is responsible for accessing the RedisGraph module commands via the Jedis programmatic library.
RedisKey
The RedisKey class handles Redis key generation and data object restoration operations.
RedisSearch
The RedisSearch class is responsible for accessing the RediSearch module commands via the Jedis programmatic library.
RedisTimeseries
The RedisTimeseries class is responsible for accessing the RedisTimeSeries module commands via the Jedis programmatic library.
SearchCriteria
This is a helper class for the RediSearch data source and should not be invoked by applications.
